From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000005 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: polyregion <noreply@polyregion>
Date: Sun, 15 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] [SPIRV] legalize a chained ptrcast user

SPIRVLegalizePointerCast::legalizePointerCast walks the users of an
spv_ptrcast and rewrites loads, stores, spv_gep and spv_store. It hit
`llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ptrcast user")` when the user was itself another
spv_ptrcast, i.e. a round-trip cast `T* -> i8* -> T*` (libstdc++ emits this for
`vector<string>::operator[]`: the loaded `_Vector_base*` is cast to i8 then back
to the struct). Route the chained cast through the original pointer exactly like
spv_gep does; the outer cast is its own worklist entry and legalises against the
real deduced type, so the redundant inner cast collapses.
---
 llvm/lib/Target/SPIRV/SPIRVLegalizePointerCast.cpp | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/llvm/lib/Target/SPIRV/SPIRVLegalizePointerCast.cpp b/llvm/lib/Target/SPIRV/SPIRVLegalizePointerCast.cpp
--- a/llvm/lib/Target/SPIRV/SPIRVLegalizePointerCast.cpp
+++ b/llvm/lib/Target/SPIRV/SPIRVLegalizePointerCast.cpp
@@ -405,7 +405,11 @@
           continue;
         }

-        if (Intrin->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::spv_gep) {
+        // A chained ptrcast (e.g. struct* -> i8* -> struct*) feeds this cast into
+        // another; route it through the original pointer so the inner cast collapses.
+        // The outer cast is its own worklist entry and legalises against the real type.
+        if (Intrin->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::spv_gep ||
+            Intrin->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::spv_ptrcast) {
           GR->replaceAllUsesWith(CastedOperand, OriginalOperand,
                                  /* DeleteOld= */ false);
           continue;
